The United Nations Population Fund (UNFPA) believes that only a complete upgrading of maternal health
services and the legal establishment of abortion could address the situation in Haiti.
For this reason, UNFPA Haiti and Spain have provided the Paris-based NGO Plan Colombia/Justice, which, in
October 1999, launched a three-year national abortion research project to help change attitude towards abortion. The
project’s main aim is to reduce, through education and public awareness, the stigma within the Haitian population
on the phenomenon of abortion. However, if abortion is not provided as an option, statistics will continue to be
reflected in the high rates of maternal morbidity and mortality that occur in Haiti. Too many Haitian women are
dying because of unsafe abortions while about 80 per cent of them do not use contraceptives routinely.
